storyInfo: Yato and Noir Corne's investigation in the Soubo Mountains yields little, until they discover massive scratch marks, strange creatures appear out of nowhere, and a shadow covers the entire sky.

attributes.content: Still no good... Stand on your toes.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Almost there. Just a little longer.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Done. You can put me down now.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Got some good samples this time.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Not that one, the blue one. Watch the category.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: So, what was it you wanted to say?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: I was just thinking, maybe we could request a ladder the next time we go on a field mission?
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Denied. Carrying too much weight reduces mobility, making it harder to deal with unexpected situations.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Check this sample too. Let's hope we find something this time.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: What would you need a ladder for anyway?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Initial tests reveal no active Originium particles, just like before.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Still nothing... How many samples have we collected?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Air, soil, organisms, surfaces... 23 samples from 17 locations in total.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: And we found nothing in any of them?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Maybe the rain from a couple of days ago affected the detection of active Originium particles.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Did you notice anything unusual along the way?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: What about those broken and charred trees?
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Probably struck by lightning in the storm... If that could be called unusual, then we'd be dealing with a fire-breathing monster on a rampage.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: I don't want to call this a waste of time, but it is seeming like gathering more samples wouldn't be the most efficient way to go about this.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Let's change our methodology. What do you think about interviewing the local Infected directly?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Tracing their movements could really help in determining the source of the Originium. But there's something we should keep in mind.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: The hilly terrain limits the contact that these villages have with the outside. The locals may not be very cooperative.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: The most recent suspected case came from Roka Village, at the bottom of this hill. Let's head there first.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Oh, huh. They reported the case directly to Rhodes Island and requested medical aid? That's rare.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Pay attention on the way down. There might be something we missed.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: 0737 hours, sunny, northern Soubo mountain range, Higashi.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: This is Yato, captain of Rhodes Island Operations Team A4, responding to Oripathy cases in the region along with Operator Noir Corne.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: There have recently been multiple cases suspected to be infection by Oripathy. We believe there to have been an abnormal spread of airborne Originium particles. We have not eliminated the possibility that this phenomenon is manmade.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: We are currently on the outskirts of the forests of Soubo. We have completed a preliminary survey of the local environment and collected some samples, but have yet to find anything unusua—
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Yato! Over here! I found something!
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: What is it? Er... is this what you found?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Some bugs under a pile of dried leaves?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Uh... it seemed strange when I first saw them, but now I've forgotten why.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Well, bring it up again when you remember... We have yet to find anything unusual and are continuing our investigation. End audio log.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: I asked Mint to recommend me a few books because the Doctor said I should read more. One of them was 'The Originium Slug's Guide to Terran Wildlife,' which was fun because it had a lot of pictures in it.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: It talked about the habitats of waterflies. Did you know that they always lay their eggs in puddles?
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: The larvae grow up in the puddles, and fly away when they're adults.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Nothing but leaves here. No puddles.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Can waterfly larvae survive in damp environments?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Wait... there are bushes around here, but pretty evenly distributed.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: So why are there so many leaves in this particular area?
attributes.name: Yato
Noir Corne
attributes.content: Hey, why are you looking at me? I don't have a shovel.
Did that book mention anything about this, Corne?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Do fowlbeasts grow this big in the mountains of Higashi?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: These claw marks are massive... similar to a fowlbeast's talons in shape, but nearly the same length as my sword, leaving deep indentations in the ground.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: A creature that can leave marks like these must be the size of a house.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Ceobe would be over the moons... One of these could feed her for days.
attributes.name: Noir Corne
Yato
attributes.content: One of these could feed on us.
Here. Don't forget your safety protocols.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: A massive creature... No records of similar claw marks, nor eyewitness reports from the surrounding areas. Did it just appear out of nowhere?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: No, we can't assume it was an animal. What would a fowlbeast that large even look like?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: And where did the Originium particles come from?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Could it be... those leaves were...?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: We need to record the scratches. Bring the equipment.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: What the heck is that, Yato?
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Some kind of local Feline variant?
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Hard to say. I've never seen a Feline like that before.
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: Hold on... look at their movements, Yato.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: They're dancing... they don't look hostile.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Hey! Who are you? Are you Felines? Do you understand what I'm saying?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: They don't seem to be Felines... are they non-sapient?
attributes.name: Yato

attributes.content: I'm not sure... something about the scratches? Or the creature that left them?
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Who are mew calling non-sapient, you rude, horned lass!
attributes.name: Strange White Creature

attributes.content: (Points towards the scratches on the ground)
attributes.name: Strange White Creature

attributes.content: It can talk! It can talk!
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: I think he just called you rude, Yato.
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: Hey! The yellow one just picked up our equipment!
attributes.name: Noir Corne

attributes.content: The events of that afternoon come flashing back from time to time.
Shoes covered in mud, 23 useless samples...
Massive scratch marks buried beneath fallen leaves, dancing furry creatures somewhat reminiscent of Felines.
No disrespect to Felines, of course.
And who could forget the massive shadow hovering over us, like a fireball ready to set the world ablaze.
